[Student "S"]
{West opens 1NT.  

This may go against your instincts, but if you're going to play Stayman then you should follow the rules. Granted that you have a great \S suit, you also have 4 \Hs. And when you have a 4-card Major you use Stayman. You bid 2\C and partner says 2\H.  

That is why you used Stayman - to uncover a 4-4 Major suit fit. Having done so you know that you will play in \Hs and you have enough points to bid game. You bid 4\H.}

